  "prompt": "How is winter in Houston?",
  "response": "Winter in Houston is generally mild compared to many other parts of the United States. Average temperatures during winter months (December through February) tend to be in the range of the mid-40s to mid-60s Fahrenheit (approximately 7 to 18 degrees Celsius), though Houston can occasionally experience colder temperatures, particularly during cold fronts.\n\nSnowfall is rare, but freezing rain and sleet can occur occasionally. Houston's winter weather often includes a mix of sunny, cool days and overcast, rainy periods. Due to the mild winter temperatures, plants and greenery in the area tend to remain vibrant year-round. However, residents should still be prepared for occasional cold snaps.",
